      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-2">How Many Days Have You Been Alive? Calculate Your Exact Age</h1>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-8">July 16, 2025 • 3 min read</p>

      <p>You know your age in years, but have you ever wondered exactly how many days you have been alive? Or how many heartbeats you have had? Here is how to calculate your precise age and some fascinating milestones to look forward to.</p>

      <h2>Quick Age-in-Days Estimates</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>1 year:</strong> 365 days</li>
        <li><strong>10 years:</strong> about 3,652 days</li>
        <li><strong>20 years:</strong> about 7,305 days</li>
        <li><strong>30 years:</strong> about 10,957 days</li>
        <li><strong>40 years:</strong> about 14,610 days</li>
        <li><strong>50 years:</strong> about 18,262 days</li>
        <li><strong>70 years:</strong> about 25,567 days</li>
      </ul>
      <p>The exact number depends on how many leap years fall within your lifetime (roughly one every 4 years adds an extra day).</p>

      <h2>Fun Age Milestones</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>1,000 days old:</strong> About 2 years 9 months — a toddler milestone</li>
        <li><strong>5,000 days old:</strong> About 13 years 8 months — early teenager</li>
        <li><strong>10,000 days old:</strong> About 27 years 5 months</li>
        <li><strong>20,000 days old:</strong> About 54 years 9 months</li>
        <li><strong>30,000 days old:</strong> About 82 years 2 months</li>
        <li><strong>1 billion seconds:</strong> About 31 years 8 months</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Your Age in Other Units</h2>
      <p>A 30-year-old has lived approximately:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Days:</strong> 10,957</li>
        <li><strong>Hours:</strong> 262,968</li>
        <li><strong>Minutes:</strong> 15,778,080</li>
        <li><strong>Seconds:</strong> 946,684,800</li>
        <li><strong>Heartbeats:</strong> about 1.1 billion (at ~72 bpm)</li>
        <li><strong>Breaths:</strong> about 237 million (at ~15 per minute)</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How Age is Counted Differently</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Western system:</strong> You are 0 at birth and turn 1 after your first full year</li>
        <li><strong>Korean age (traditional):</strong> You are 1 at birth and everyone gains a year on New Year's Day</li>
        <li><strong>Chinese age:</strong> Similar to Korean — based on lunar calendar</li>
        <li><strong>Note:</strong> South Korea officially adopted the Western system in 2023</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Leap Year Birthdays</h2>
      <p>Born on February 29? You only get a "real" birthday every 4 years. Legally, most countries consider March 1 as your birthday in non-leap years. If you are 40 years old but born on Feb 29, you have technically had only 10 actual birthdays.</p>

